HEADWORD: Caprimulgiformes
<hw>Caprimulgiformes</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an order of birds including
the goatsuckers (<fam>Caprimulgidae</fam>), frogmouths, and the oilbird
(guacharo) (family <fam>Steatornithidae</fam>).</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> order <ord>Caprimulgiformes</ord>.</syn>⟦br⟧
